ents.%20The%20scheme%2C%20named%20%26quot%3BSatyug%20Gold%2C%26quot%3B%20allegedly%20assured%20investors%20of%20gold%20delivery%20at%20a%20fixed%20rate%2C%20regardless%20of%20market%20fluctuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kothari%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20players%20in%20the%20gold%20and%20bullion%20market%2C%20claims%20to%20have%20been%20persuaded%20by%20the%20accused%20to%20invest%20a%20substantial%20amount%20in%20the%20scheme.%20Assurances%20from%20Ms%20Shetty%2C%20Mr%20Kundra%2C%20and%20their%20associates%20reportedly%20convinced%20him%20of%20the%20scheme's%20legitimacy%20and%20the%20timely%20delivery%20of%20gold%20upon%20maturity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20upon%20reaching%20the%20maturity%20date%20of%20April%202%2C%202019%2C%20Mr%20Kothari%20alleges%20that%20he%20did%20not%20receive%20the%20promised%20gold%20despite%20his%20upfront%20payment%20of%20Rs%2090%2C38%2C600.%20Documents%20presented%20by%20the%20complainant%2C%20including%20a%20covering%20letter%20signed%20by%20Shilpa%20Shetty%20Kundra%20and%20an%20invoice%20issued%20by%20Satyug%20Gold%20Private%20Limited%2C%20seemingly%20support%20his%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%2C%20as%20described%20by%20Mr%20Kothari%2C%20appeared%20to%20offer%20a%20secure%20investment%20opportunity%2C%20buoyed%20by%20the%20reputation%20of%20Shilpa%20Shetty%20and%20Raj%20Kundra%20in%20the%20entertainment%20and%20business%20spheres%2C%20respectively.%20Investors%20were%20led%20to%20believe%20that%20their%20investments%20were%20safeguarded%20by%20the%20stature%20of%20the%20accused%20individuals%2C%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20allegedly%20defrauded%20in%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20directed%20Mumbai%20Police%20to%20investigate%20the%20allegations%20made%20in%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Raj%20Kundra%20landed%20on%20the%20radar%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case%20linked%20to%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme.%20The%20probe%20