0cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20described%20the%20incident%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmp.weixin.qq.com%2Fs%2FQD8MOVukB7gHlQ3p2qnZaQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20post%20%3C%2Fa%3Eencouraging%20the%20public%20to%20be%20vigilant%20on%20national%20security%20matters%2C%20and%20praised%20the%20retiree%20for%20reporting%20the%20documents%20to%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20identified%20as%20%26quot%3BGrandpa%20Zhang.%26quot%3B%20Chinese%20authorities%20and%20media%20typically%20do%20not%20publish%20the%20full%20names%20of%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20a%20high%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20post%2C%20Zhang%20is%20a%20former%20employee%20of%20a%20state-owned%20enterprise%20and%20collects%20military%20newspapers%20and%20magazines%20as%20a%20hobby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20walking%20in%20his%20neighborhood%20when%20he%20passed%20a%20scrap%20store%20selling%20two%20bags%20filled%20with%20books%20that%20seemed%20related%20to%20the%20military%2C%20per%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcited%20with%20his%20find%2C%20he%20paid%20about%206%20Chinese%20yuan%2C%20or%20%240.85%2C%20for%20one%20bag%20of%20four%20volumes%20and%20brought%20them%20home%2C%20according%20to%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20Zhang%20studied%20the%20books%2C%20realized%20they%20were%20marked%20as%20%26quot%3Bconfidential%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsecret%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20reported%20them%20to%20a%20public%20security%20hotline%2C%20authorities%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Security%20Ministry%20said%20agents%20rushed%20to%20Zhang's%20home%20and%20seized%20the%20documents.%20The%20ministry%20did%20not%20say%20where%20Zhang%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpon%20investigating%20the%20scrap%20store%2C%20the%20state%20security%20ministry%20discovered%20that%20Zhang's%20purchase%20had%20been%20part%20of%20eight%20volumes%20of%20200%20secret%20documents%20marked%20for%20disposal%2C%20the%20post%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20two%20military%20personnel%20in%20a%20classified%20unit%2C%20who%20were%20identified%20only%20as%20Guo%20and%20Li%2C%20were%20tasked%20with%20shredding%20the%20documents%20but%20instead%20sold%20them%20to%20a%20recycling%20plant%20for%20about%20%240.06%20per%20pound.%20The%20entire%20tranche%20of%20documents%20weighed%20about%2060%20pounds%2C%20meaning%20the%20duo%20made%20a%20profit%20of%20less%20than%20%244%20for%20the%20entire%20sale%2C%20authorities%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20criticized%20the%20pair%20as%20having%20a%20%26quot%3Bweak%20sense%20of%20confidentiality%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgreed%20for%20convenience's%20sake%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20that%20the%20incident%20did%20not%20create%20a%20significant%20intelligence%20leak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20Guo%20and%20Li%2C%20as%20well%20as%20anyone%20else%20responsible%2C%20were%20dealt%20with%20under%20Chinese%20law%20and%20that%20the%20ministry%20oversaw%20a%20revamp%20of%20procedures%20to%20avoid%20similar%20gaffes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20on%20Thursday%20was%20part%20of%20a%20push%20by%20the%20State%20Security%20Ministry%20to%20promote%20a%20hotline%20that%20Chinese%20people%20can%20use%20to%20report%20national%20security%20lapses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20what%20information%20the%20documents%20mentioned%20by%20the%20ministry%20contained%2C%20so%20it's%20difficult%20to%20say%20how%20a%20leak%20of%20such%20secrets%20may%20have%20affected%20the%20Chinese%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20State%20Security%20Ministry%20has%2C%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20regularly%20urged%20the%20public%20to%20assist%20in%20reporting%20foreign%20espionage.%20In%20April%202023%2C%20Beijing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-business-risks-sanctions-detentions-us-tensions-espionage-law-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20its%20anti-espionage%20law.%3C%2Fa%3E%20These%20changes%20broadened%20the